Information for the volleyball game August 27th @Wymore
6:00 pm Falls city vs Johnson-Brock
7:00 pm Southern vs Johnson-Brock

Each school will need to submit a fan list of 115 individuals who will be attending the game. This will be the only fans that will be allowed to attend the games. All fans in attendance must be wearing masks. The only exception will be individuals under the age of 5.

Family members must sit together(Social distancing of 6 feet between family groups must be maintained.)

Bleachers will be blocked off every other row. We will have an area around the benches that will be clear for the teams.

Limited concessions will be available during the game and we do ask that those in line also maintain social distancing.

post_text:
Check this out Eagles!
In partnership with EVERFI, Major League Baseball’s Summer Slugger program was developed to combat summer learning loss during vacation months, but is even more relevant for students now when they may struggle with knowledge retention due to school closures. The course -- designed for children 8-11 years old -- focuses on math & literacy skills and teaches these concepts through a baseball-themed, game experience.

Website: SummerSlugger.com/Royals Team Code: royals

About Summer Slugger

Summer Slugger is an evidence-based program that provides students with baseball-themed math and literacy activities aimed to support retention of knowledge during the summer. The digital resource, intended for children ages 8-11, engages students in game-based activities that address the skills necessary to combat the loss of knowledge over the summer. Since 2017, 140,000 students across MLB’s 30 markets participated in Summer Slugger.

post_text:
BARN QUILT LIVE AUCTION

The Johnson-Brock Teammates will be auctioning off 2ft x 2ft Barn Quilts hand painted by Mentors and Mentees during their December gatherings. The quilts will be live auctioned by Mentee Dacota Falk during four upcoming home basketball games. A total of 8 Barn Quilts (2 at each game) will be auctioned off between the varsity girls’ and boys’ basketball games on January 7, 11, and 24, 2020. These hand painted quilts will be on display during these home games. This is a fundraiser for the Johnson-Brock Teammates Chapter with funds being designated towards scholarships for graduating Mentees.

Please come support your local Teammates chapter, Mentees, and Mentors by bidding on these beautiful Barn Quilts. The memories made will last a lifetime!

(The attached photo shows Wayne Koehler (Mentor) , Zach and Peyton (Mentees) with one of the 2 ft x 2 ft Barn Quilts that will be auctioned off at an upcoming home basketball game)

Tera Stutheit is with Jen Simpson Kahland.
December 11, 2019 at 8:26 PM ·

A fantastic season! 3rd at state! I feel blessed to be part of such a wonderful group of kids who always go the extra mile. We performed today on about six hours of sleep and they rocked it! Thanks to everyone who made the trip today and to parents who had snacks for us. We appreciate your support more than you’ll
ever know!

Congrats Elaina Riley, Ty Hahn, & Josh Hoff-Boring for receiving Outatanding Performance Awards.

Special thanks to Jeffrey Koehler, Ami Koehler, Wayne Koehler, and Mason Benham for unloading our set trailer tonight!

Special thanks to Cec Antholz for designing and making several costumes again this season. And to Ruth Denny Norvell for helping maintain costumes! And thanks to everyone at school for always pitching in to help with our weird random requests throughout the season. JB is the best!
Johnson-Brock Public School
Tara Rose Gossman

post_text:
During 2019 Box Tops for Education is going digital. The first digital Box Tops appeared in August. Box
Tops is making this change to decrease the load on the coordinator and to reduce their carbon
footprint in the printing and shipping of the clips.
When you buy a product on line, you can earn points on eligible items right away by designating a
school. When you buy in store, you can scan your receipt and apply Box Tops points to the school of
your choice.
Physical Box Tops clips will be accepted by the program up to the final expiration date. So if you have
Box Tops clips be sure to send those to the school. Also, for a limited time you can double down on
Box Tops by submitting digitally and sending the clips to the school.
To get started go to boxtops4education.com and register as a user. All the information you need can
be found here. There are commonly asked questions and instructions for use.
Thank you for supporting Johnson-Brock through the Box Tops Program!

post_text: Congratulations Eagles with the win tonight over Pawnee City. Girls will play Thursday at 7pm in Southern vs Diller Odell

post_text: The MUDECAS boys basketball games scheduled for tonight have been cancelled due to the weather. There will not be makeup dates for the games.

post_text:
The Eagles started off the night with girls Jr High wins over HTRS followed by girls jv, girls varsity and boys varsity all over HTRS.
Subs will start for the girls Tuesday at Southern vs Pawnee City while boys will play Freeman for Mudecas in the consolation game Monday night in Southern.

post_text: Kids are arriving and all of the buses are here! Thanks parents for getting everyone going this morning and helping transport students to school that needed rides. Kids are warm and going to have a great day!

post_text:
The forecast for tomorrow morning is calling for -20 at 7am and by 10am they are predicting -7 so Johnson-Brock will have a two hr late start.
The building will be open at 7:30am so that working families can drop off their children and not have to walk to school. Breakfast will not be served Again parents always have the final decision to send their children to school or keep them at home.
